CatDescriptText: Cornelius Scully was Mayor of the City of Pittsburgh from 1936 to 1945.
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Mayor Cornelius D. Scully and Director of Public Safety Col. George Fairley, administering oath to man with two other men, model of Independence Hall, and poster "We the People...for Defense", in the Office of the Mayor at the City County Building
